org.apache.flink.runtime.io.network.api

Class RecordReader<T extends IOReadableWritable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flink.runtime.io.network.api.AbstractRecordReader
      • org.apache.flink.runtime.io.network.api.AbstractSingleGateRecordReader<T>
        • org.apache.flink.runtime.io.network.api.RecordReader<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the record that can be read from this record reader.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Reader<T>, ReaderBase

    public class RecordReader<T extends IOReadableWritable>
extends AbstractSingleGateRecordReader<T>
implements Reader<T>
    A record writer connects an input gate to an application. It allows the application query for incoming records and read them from input gate.
